  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dbd\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dba \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7 50\u0d9a \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "National Fuel License Fuel stations are 50 percent operational",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, Minister of Electricity and Energy, says that there has been a successful development in the distribution of fuel through the National Fuel Licence.",
        "According to the minister, almost 50 percent of the petrol stations in Sri Lanka are currently operating under that system.",
        "Thus, Cipetco has 409 gas stations and I.O.C. The minister mentioned that this system was implemented in 72 gas stations and the number of transactions that took place was 158,208.",
        "Motorcycles are the most registered for the National Fuel License and the number is more than 24 lakh.",
        "He also said that 4.25 million vehicles had been registered under the National Fuel Permit system by 8.30 last night."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "50 percent",
          "label": "PERCENT"
        }
      ],
